The paper discusses the problem of learning joint probability measures on a large set of variables, which is a common topic in machine learning and statistics. Specifically, the paper focuses on the case of learning sparse Bayesian networks with bounded in-degree, which is a well-studied problem in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves some graph theory and combinatorics, which could place it in the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
